HIV/AIDS: China ta ce ta samu karuwar 14 cikin 100 na sababbin kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ce yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya ƙaru zuwa kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Masu kula da lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 suna fama da wannan cuta.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekara ta 2018 kaɗai, an yi rahoton kusan sababbin shari'o'i 40,000.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun fito ne daga yin jima'i, kuma hakan ya canja rayuwarmu.
A wasu sassa na ƙasar Sin , an yi amfani da jini don yaduwar cutar HIV .
Amma, a wannan hanyar, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka tabbatar a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
A shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yada cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An kafa doka a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma ana zargin cewa an nuna bambanci sosai ga 'yan luwadi.
Domin irin ƙa'idodin da ƙasar take da shi, bincike ya nuna cewa maza 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aure mata.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne domin rashin kāriya ta jima'i daga irin wannan dangantaka.
Tun daga shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin Sin ta ba da izinin yin amfani da maganin HIV a duniya don magance matsalar.
